DOROTHEA: Need we relive this?

MADELEINE: “Whatever injuries and indignities the women suffered, were the outcome of their invitation to all and sundry to assemble and make common cause against the Government. Their sympathisers included undesirable and reckless persons, quite capable of indulging in gross conduct, and for their presence in Parliament Square the women were themselves responsible.”

DOROTHEA: I know it hurts, sister, but at least we won. Look, in 2022 a woman is leading Britain. We may be villains now but in their time, perhaps we’re heroes.

MADELEINE: What good is that title when I know who I’m sharing it with? What is a hero? DOROTHEA: I believe it’s a leader who changes the lives of many for the better. Like Emmeline
Pankhurst.

MADELEINE: Well, I think it’s ordinary people who sacrifice everything for a greater cause. Like all the women we fight with. Not like Mr Winston Churchill.

